#### ❓ What does the `key` prop do in React lists?

- [ ] A. Styles the element
- [ ] B. Helps React identify which items changed, were added, or removed
- [ ] C. Prevents re-renders entirely
- [ ] D. Sets an element's CSS class

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Helps React identify which items changed, were added, or removed**

Keys allow React to track elements across renders. Without stable keys, React may unnecessarily re-create DOM nodes or show stale data during list updates.

</details>

