#### ❓ What is the problem with using array index as a `key` in lists?

- [ ] A. It is not a valid JavaScript value
- [ ] B. It can cause UI bugs when items are reordered, inserted, or deleted
- [ ] C. It forces re-renders on every change
- [ ] D. There is no problem; it is the recommended approach

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. It can cause UI bugs when items are reordered, inserted, or deleted**

When items are reordered, the same index maps to a different item, confusing React's diffing algorithm and causing incorrect component state or visual glitches.

</details>

