#### ❓ What is the difference between `props` and `state`?

- [ ] A. Props are mutable; state is immutable
- [ ] B. Props are passed from parent to child and read-only; state is managed internally and can change
- [ ] C. State is passed from parent to child; props are internal
- [ ] D. They are interchangeable

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Props are passed from parent to child and read-only; state is managed internally and can change**

Props flow downward and a component cannot modify its own props. State is local, mutable, and triggers re-renders when updated.

</details>

