### 🔹 Hooks

#### ❓ What is the purpose of `useEffect`?

- [ ] A. To manage state
- [ ] B. To handle side effects (data fetching, subscriptions, DOM manipulation)
- [ ] C. To create components
- [ ] D. To optimize rendering

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. To handle side effects (data fetching, subscriptions, DOM manipulation)**

`useEffect` runs after render and is used for side effects. The dependency array controls when it re-runs.

</details>

---

#### ❓ When does `useEffect` run with an empty dependency array `[]`?

- [ ] A. On every render
- [ ] B. Never
- [ ] C. Only once after the initial render (mount)
- [ ] D. Only when the component unmounts

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**C. Only once after the initial render (mount)**

An empty dependency array tells React there are no dependencies, so the effect runs once on mount and the cleanup runs on unmount.

</details>

---

#### ❓ What does the cleanup function returned from `useEffect` do?

- [ ] A. Deletes component state
- [ ] B. Runs before the next effect execution or when the component unmounts, used to cancel subscriptions/timers
- [ ] C. Prevents the effect from running
- [ ] D. Resets the dependency array

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Runs before the next effect execution or when the component unmounts, used to cancel subscriptions/timers**

The cleanup function prevents memory leaks by clearing timeouts, canceling subscriptions, or aborting fetch requests before re-running the effect or unmounting.

</details>

