#### ❓ What is a custom hook?

- [ ] A. A hook created by the React team for special use cases
- [ ] B. A JavaScript function whose name starts with `use` and can call other hooks to encapsulate reusable logic
- [ ] C. A hook only available in class components
- [ ] D. A third-party library hook

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. A JavaScript function whose name starts with `use` and can call other hooks to encapsulate reusable logic**

Custom hooks extract component logic into reusable functions. Examples: `useFetch`, `useLocalStorage`, `useDebounce`.

</details>

