#### ❓ What does `shouldComponentUpdate` do?

- [ ] A. Prevents the component from ever rendering
- [ ] B. Lets you bail out of re-rendering by returning `false` when props/state haven't meaningfully changed
- [ ] C. Forces a re-render
- [ ] D. Fetches data before rendering

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Lets you bail out of re-rendering by returning `false` when props/state haven't meaningfully changed**

`PureComponent` implements a shallow version of this automatically. In function components, `React.memo` serves the same purpose.

</details>

