#### ❓ What is an Error Boundary in React?

- [ ] A. A try/catch statement in a hook
- [ ] B. A class component that catches JavaScript errors in its child tree and renders a fallback UI
- [ ] C. A TypeScript type guard
- [ ] D. A network error handler

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. A class component that catches JavaScript errors in its child tree and renders a fallback UI**

Error boundaries use `componentDidCatch` and `getDerivedStateFromError`. As of React 19, there is also a new `use()` hook for async error boundaries.

</details>

