- [ ] A. A newer version of HTML
- [ ] B. A binary protocol supporting multiplexing, server push, and header compression — reducing latency
- [ ] C. A replacement for HTTPS
- [ ] D. A WebSocket alternative

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. A binary protocol supporting multiplexing, server push, and header compression — reducing latency**

HTTP/2 allows multiple requests on a single connection (no head-of-line blocking), eliminating the need for domain sharding and request bundling workarounds.

</details>

