## 🤖 Next.js & SSR

### 🔹 Rendering Strategies

#### ❓ What is Server-Side Rendering (SSR)?

- [ ] A. Rendering components only on the client
- [ ] B. Generating HTML on the server for each request and sending it to the client
- [ ] C. Pre-rendering at build time
- [ ] D. Rendering in a web worker

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Generating HTML on the server for each request and sending it to the client**

SSR provides fast initial page loads and good SEO. The trade-off is server processing per request.

</details>

---

#### ❓ What is Static Site Generation (SSG)?

- [ ] A. Rendering on every request
- [ ] B. Pre-rendering pages at build time into static HTML files
- [ ] C. Rendering only on the client
- [ ] D. Streaming HTML from the server

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Pre-rendering pages at build time into static HTML files**

SSG is the fastest delivery method (files can be served from CDN), best for pages that don't change per user/request.

</details>

---

#### ❓ What is Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR) in Next.js?

- [ ] A. Rebuilding the entire site on every change
- [ ] B. Regenerating specific static pages in the background after a revalidation period without a full rebuild
- [ ] C. Client-side rendering with caching
- [ ] D. A progressive image loading technique

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Regenerating specific static pages in the background after a revalidation period without a full rebuild**

ISR provides the performance of static pages with the freshness of SSR using `revalidate` in `getStaticProps`.

</details>

---

#### ❓ What are React Server Components (RSC)?

- [ ] A. Components that only work in Node.js
- [ ] B. Components that render exclusively on the server, can directly access backend resources, and send no JavaScript to the client
- [ ] C. SSR components that hydrate on the client
- [ ] D. A React Native feature

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. Components that render exclusively on the server, can directly access backend resources, and send no JavaScript to the client**

RSCs reduce client bundle size significantly. They cannot use hooks or browser APIs. Client components opt-in with `"use client"`.

</details>

---

#### ❓ What is hydration in SSR?

- [ ] A. Downloading CSS files
- [ ] B. The process where React attaches event listeners to server-rendered HTML to make it interactive
- [ ] C. Converting JSON to HTML
- [ ] D. A caching mechanism

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>

**B. The process where React attaches event listeners to server-rendered HTML to make it interactive**

Hydration mismatch errors occur when the server-rendered HTML differs from what React would render on the client.

</details>

